ed as part of NPM, with codes of ethics a means of regulating and controlling the conduct of professionals and service users. She emphasises the importance of reclaiming professional ethics for social work, and outlines a preliminary framework for a situated ethics of social justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBanks, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBanks, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBeckett, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlackledge, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBozalek, Vivienne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCowden, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIto, Fumihito, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReamer, Frederic G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReisch, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeinberg, Merlinda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144731618340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/978144736665240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447366652423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447366652/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013